Renault sees investment slowing . French carmaker Renault SA said on Thursday its investments totalled 16 . 39 billion francs last year , around nine percent of sales , but expects that proportion to ease in coming years to between six and seven percent . Chairman Louis Schweitzer said last year ' s investment , up from 15 . 26 billion francs in 1995 , marked the end of a surge related to product renewals . " We expect to bring it ( investment ) to six to seven percent of sales , " he told reporters at a briefing on the carmaker ' s 1996 results . ( ( - - Paris Newsroom , + 33 1 4221 5452 ) ) 
